# Test Documentation Structure

## Directory layout (canonical)
- `docs/` — Test strategy, critical paths, test plans, reports.
  - `docs/02-critical-paths.md` — List of critical paths and ownership.
  - `docs/test-plans/<feature-slug>-plan.md` — Per-feature test plans.
  - `docs/reports/` — Release readiness, triage reports (e.g. `release-readiness-<date>.md`).
- `testcases/exploratory/` — Charters and session notes (`<feature>-charter.md`).
- `testcases/manual/` — Manual test cases: `CP-<id>-<slug>.md` (critical path), `REG-<bug-id>-<slug>.md` (regression), or `<feature>-<id>.md`.
- `automation/playwright/tests/` — Smoke (`smoke/`), E2E (`e2e/`), regression (`regression/`).

## Naming
- Use lowercase slugs; hyphens for multi-word (e.g. `login`, `checkout-flow`, `REG-123-cart-total`).
- No PII in file names or content; use placeholders in examples.

## When adding tests or docs
- Create the appropriate file under the paths above.
- If adding a critical path: update `docs/02-critical-paths.md`.
- If adding a regression: use `REG-` prefix and optional link to bug id in the file.
